				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Playing songs while fighting question...<a name="9326"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 03 12:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In all the hundreds of hours I have played, I have not noticed any difference in missed notes whether auto-attack is on versus off.
<br />

<br />
However, I have a fast computer and a fast connection, and it does seem that I miss more notes in high-lag areas, ie like in Ssra basement during an AoE-fest.  If you have a slower system, and connection that may be enough to make a difference somewhere like DL.  The &quot;Your target is too far away&quot; messages do add more lag, not an appreciable amount, but some.  More lag = more missed notes in my experiance.</span></td>
