				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Playing songs while fighting question...<a name="9345"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 03 10:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In my experience: the weather, time of day, phase of the moon, direness of the circumstances, and whether or not you are paying attention to the casting bar &amp; spam window all affect 'missed notes'.
<br />

<br />
According to some recent in-depth research at 'The Concert Hall' its only level and charisma.
<br />

<br />
According to Sony in the new character creation hints, its dexterity and charisma (other Intelligence based casters have their 'fizzle' rate affected by Int, but according to these hints, that does NOT include bards).
<br />

<br />
Some folks believe you get more missed notes when you first receive a song than as you level (also more resists).
<br />

<br />
As to auto attack affecting it, I would hope not, but after reading the bug fix reports, evidently, anything is possible.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
