				<td colspan="2"><span>On page 27 of the book that came with your PoP expansion, it gives explanation of different stats...there it states Charisma effects the number of missed notes. 
<br />
On the new character creation screen, click on charisma, and it will tell you that Charisma effects the number of missed notes. 
<br />
Don't know how many times I've had this conversation. Ever since the creation of bards, we have always been told that charisma was important, though we all seem to believe that it is only for Mezzes and Charms...neither of which you do on a full time basis, whereas, we sing constantly. 
<br />
Any raid group or exp group, I always get Charisma buff to max it out, so honestly, I cant tell you the difference on the missed notes cept for that 30minutes or so it takes to convince them that I need that buff. 
<br />
I have gotten up to *ouch* 5 missed notes IN A ROW. Whence, after getting my Charisma buff from the local Shaman or Chanter, I wont miss a single note for 2 hours or more. Half the time, I can tell that my buff wore off, cause I missed a note.....
<br />

<br />
Charisma and Dexterity - always have been and always will be the most important and benefitial stats for the twisting bard.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"><u><b>Dexterity:</b></u> Dexterity affects how quickly you learn weapon skills, and how often weapons will do their special.  For Bards it also effects their chance of missing notes (fizzling) their spells.  This is a critical statistic for Bards and one which they should certainly raise with their extra points.
<br />

<br />
<u><b>Charisma:</b></u> This affects amount you will be paid for goods by NPC merchants, and how much they will pay you.  It also affects the saving throw on certain Bard and Enchanter spells (charms in particular).  For Bards, Charisma is much more important than for other classes.  It not only effects their chance of songs being resisted, but also is part of the calculation for fizzled notes.  Points should definitely be spent increasing this statistic at creation.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
quotes stolen from <a target="_new" href="http://eq.crgaming.com/creationguides/bard.asp">http://eq.crgaming.com/creationguides/bard.asp</a>
